  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000 while serving in the professional capacity of an accountant. However, mitigating factors must be considered, including the defendant's lack of a prior criminal record and the fact that partial restitution has already been made, showing some level of remorse and responsibility. The outburst from the spectator has no bearing on the legal determination of the sentence. Balancing the breach of trust against the mitigating factors, an eight-month sentence of incarceration is appropriate to serve as both punishment and a deterrent.",
  "verdict": 8
}
